.TH "TOLLGATE" "8" "Jul 2026" "tollgate-wrt" "TollGate OpenWrt Module"

.SH NAME
.PP
tollgate-completion-fish - Generate the autocompletion script for fish


.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBtollgate completion fish [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Generate the autocompletion script for the fish shell.

.PP
To load completions in your current shell session:

.EX
tollgate completion fish | source

.EE

.PP
To load completions for every new session, execute once:

.EX
tollgate completion fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/tollgate.fish

.EE

.PP
You will need to start a new shell for this setup to take effect.


.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for fish

.PP
\fB--no-descriptions\fP[=false]
	disable completion descriptions


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
.PP
\fB-j\fP, \fB--json\fP[=false]
	Output results as JSON


